The oldest members of the following generation, " Generation Y ," (1982-2001?) are not yet eligible for election to the Senate (which has a minimum age of thirty), and will not be eligible until 2012 .
List of current United States Senators by age and generation

Using the generational boundaries as identified by authors William Strauss and Neil Howe , in their book Generations ( ISBN 0-688-11912-3 ) (1992), the generational breakdown of the Senate for the 110th Congress is as follows:
Below is a list of all the Senators serving in the 110th Congress, sorted by birth year (compiled from the individual Wikipedia pages.)
